# .cursorrules — MasterNode AI Landing Page

## Project Identity
- **Product**: MasterNode AI — Premium AI consulting firm landing page
- **Stack**: React 18 + Vite 7 + Tailwind CSS 3 + TypeScript 5
- **Owner**: Sam (senior Drupal dev, learning React/TS)

## Code Style Rules

### TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled (tsconfig strict: true)
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for component props
- Export named components, not default (except App.tsx)
- Use `type` imports: `import type { Theme } from "@/hooks/useTheme"`

### React
- Functional components only — no class components
- Hooks at the top of the function body
- Destructure props in the function signature
- Every component file has a JSDoc comment block at the top explaining purpose

### File Organization
- **One component per file** — never combine multiple exports in one .tsx
- **Every component gets its own kebab-case directory** with:
  - `ComponentName.tsx` — PascalCase filename
  - `index.ts` — barrel export
- **Import from directories**, never from files directly:
  ```tsx
  // ✅ Correct
  import { Pricing } from "@/components/sections/pricing";
  // ❌ Wrong
  import { Pricing } from "@/components/sections/pricing/Pricing";
  ```

### Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline CSS objects unless for dynamic CSS variables
- Use MasterNode design tokens: `text-mn-electric`, `bg-mn-navy`, etc.
- Never use raw hex/rgb colors — always go through CSS custom properties
- Warm accent (`mn-warm`) on max ~15% of interactive elements
- Use utility classes from index.css: `.glass`, `.text-gradient`, `.glow-accent`

### Content
- **All static text lives in `src/data/`** — never hardcode strings in components
- Exception: Tailwind class strings and HTML structure stay in components
- When adding new content, create/extend a data file, don't inline it

## Directory Map

```
src/
├── main.tsx              # Entry — do NOT add logic here
├── App.tsx               # Section composition — add new sections here
├── styles/index.css      # Theme vars + utilities — add new tokens here
├── lib/utils.ts          # cn() helper — rarely needs changes
├── hooks/                # Custom hooks
├── data/                 # ★ CONTENT LIVES HERE — edit for copy changes ★
├── components/
│   ├── ui/               # shadcn primitives — don't modify
│   ├── layout/           # announcement-bar, navbar, footer
│   ├── sections/         # 11 page sections (see render order below)
│   └── shared/           # Reusable: section-wrapper, animated-counter, etc.
```

