## Common Patterns

### Adding a new section
```bash
mkdir src/components/sections/my-section
```
Create `MySection.tsx` + `index.ts`, import in `App.tsx`.

### Wrapping a section with consistent layout
```tsx
import { SectionWrapper, SectionHeader } from "@/components/shared/section-wrapper";

export function MySection() {
  return (
    <SectionWrapper id="my-section" bgEffect="mesh-1">
      <SectionHeader
        eyebrow="Label"
        title="Main Title"
        titleAccent="Gradient Part."
        subtitle="Description text."
      />
      {/* Section content */}
    </SectionWrapper>
  );
}
```

### Using warm accent (sparingly)
```tsx
// Icons — alternate between electric and warm
<Icon className={index % 2 === 0 ? "text-mn-electric" : "text-mn-warm"} />

// Hover borders
className="hover:border-mn-warm/25 hover:shadow-mn-warm/5"

// Background gradients
className="from-mn-warm/20 to-mn-warm/5"
```

## Don'ts

- Don't use `localStorage` or `sessionStorage` — state is ephemeral
- Don't add new shadcn/ui components without confirming necessity
- Don't use Next.js patterns (no `page.tsx`, no `app/` router, no SSR)
- Don't hardcode colors — always use `mn-*` tokens
- Don't put content strings in component files — use `src/data/`
- Don't create monolithic multi-component files — split and barrel-export
- Don't modify shadcn `ui/` files directly

## Build & Deploy

```bash
npm install          # First time setup
npm run dev          # Dev server with HMR
npm run build        # Production build → /dist
```

Deploy `/dist` to Vercel, Netlify, or any static host. Framework auto-detected as Vite.
